                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sheṭar</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">שטר</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Hebrew quitclaim by Jacob ben Aaron releasing a piece of land to William le Briel.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The quitclaim is written on a small piece of parchment attached as a tag to a seal of a Latin grantc charter: Harley Ch. 77. D. 39. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The Latin grant is about a sale of a land by Walter de Colverhode and his wife Blanchia to William son of Godfried Braciator. This land must have been previously mortgaged by Walter as a surety for a loan granted by Jacob ben Aaron (see, J. Olszowy-Schlanger 2015, v.2, p. 564).</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
